PUPPET
- declarative language
- desired end state of nodes
- code written inside classes, applied to nodes

TEST PUPPET CODE:
RSpec: Testing puppet code
Beaker: testing Serverspec, spin up a node and test the node
- Use Ruby to exted Puppet modules

MODULES: forge.puppet.com
Ex. Search for Apache module

CATALOG:
- Describes the desired state of a node
  - Can contain dependencies
- Compiled version of DSL from the Puppet Master
- Stored in PuppetDB

SELinux:
- Set SELinux to permessive

$vi /etc/selinux/config
SELINUX=permissive

REBOOT the instance
-> NOW it would be able to start Puppet
